Package: aims-os-bigdata
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 aims-os-math,
# --- Big Data / data engineering (Data Mining & Big Data Analytics) --
# dask + distributed — parallel pandas / numpy across cores and nodes.
# NOTE: PyArrow, Polars and DuckDB are NOT packaged in Trixie main
# (verified 2026-05-22). They are install-on-demand via
# `pipx install` or `mamba install -c conda-forge`. We keep them
# documented here because they're course-critical.
 python3-dask,
 python3-distributed,
# --- Natural Language Processing (NLP, Generative AI courses) -------
# nltk — the teaching toolkit; every NLP textbook uses it.
# NOTE: spaCy, gensim and HuggingFace Transformers are NOT packaged in
# Trixie main (verified 2026-05-22). They evolve faster than Debian's
# release cadence — install-on-demand via
# `pipx install spacy gensim transformers` or
# `mamba install -c conda-forge spacy gensim transformers`.
 python3-nltk,
# --- Computer Vision (Computer Vision course) ------------------------
# opencv (cv2) — the standard CV library. scikit-image (in aims-os-math)
#     handles the science-y side; OpenCV handles the engineering side
#     (video I/O, feature detection, calibration).
 python3-opencv,
# --- Climate / geosciences (Climate Dynamic, Math Methods for Climate)
# xarray — labelled multi-dimensional arrays; the de-facto standard
#     for climate model output and reanalysis data.
# netcdf4 — NetCDF file format reader (every climate dataset uses it).
# cartopy — geographic projections / map plotting on top of matplotlib.
 python3-xarray,
 python3-netcdf4,
 python3-cartopy,
# --- Databases (Database course) -------------------------------------
# postgresql-client, mariadb-client, redis-tools — connect to the
#     three reference servers without pulling the daemons themselves
#     (lab uses external DB hosts).
# psycopg2 + pymongo — Python drivers for PostgreSQL and MongoDB.
 postgresql-client,
 mariadb-client,
 redis-tools,
 python3-psycopg2,
 python3-pymongo,
Description: AIMS OS — Coop Big Data track
 Adds the Big Data / data engineering layer required by the AIMS Coop
 Big Data filière on top of aims-os-math: Dask + distributed for
 parallel pandas/numpy across cores and nodes; NLTK for the Natural
 Language Processing course; OpenCV for the Computer Vision course;
 xarray, netCDF4 and Cartopy for the Climate Dynamic and Mathematical
 Methods for Climate courses; PostgreSQL, MariaDB, Redis and MongoDB
 clients (plus psycopg2 and pymongo Python drivers) for the Database
 course — clients only, the labs talk to external DB hosts.
 .
 PyArrow, Polars, DuckDB, spaCy, gensim and HuggingFace Transformers
 are deliberately NOT shipped here — none are packaged in Trixie main
 and all evolve faster than the Debian release cadence. Install on
 demand via `pipx install <name>` or
 `mamba install -c conda-forge <name>` (Miniforge3 ships in
 aims-os-core).
 .
 This metapackage Depends on aims-os-math, so installing it on a
 vanilla Debian Trixie pulls the full SciPy / R / LaTeX scientific
 stack as well. Regular-track students who don't need Big Data tooling
 should install aims-os-math directly.
